Description




 We currently have a vacancy for an
 **ETL Developer** 
 fluent in English, to offer his/her services as an expert who will be based in Stockholm, Sweden. The work will be carried out either in the company’s premises or on site at customer premises. In the context of the first assignment, the successful candidate will be integrated in the Development team of the company that will closely cooperate with a major client’s IT team on site.




**Your tasks** 




 Data modelling and data warehouse architecture;




 Design and develop new and optimize existing ETL flows for system integration, automated dataflows, data validation and storage;




 Contribute to the design of the overall solution architecture, interfaces, services, infrastructure configuration, security and access policies;




 Optimize performance of new and existing ETL flows;




 Testing ETL solutions and integration testing individually or in collaboration with other teams;




 FME flow management of workflows, job scheduling, resource allocation, error handling, monitoring, ensuring scalability.




**Requirements** 




 University degree in computer science (or equivalent) with minimum 3 years of experience in IT OR non university degree with minimum 6 years of experience in IT;




 At least 3 years of experience as ETL developer/Engineer developer using FME;




 At least 3 years of experience using SQL of which a minimum of 1 year using TransactSQL;




 Experience in FME flow management of workflows, job scheduling, resource allocation, error handling, monitoring,ensuring scalability;




 Experience in performance optimisation of ETL flows;




 Experience in data modelling and data warehouse architecture;




 Knowledge of the software development lifecycle in both: waterfall and Agile/DevOps modes;




 Experience working with work item management tool ( Azure DevOps);




 Experience producing and maintaining technical documentation;




 Experience of working in an Agile environment;




 Experience with DevOps practices, CI/CD and automation;




 Advanced TransactSQL skills and experience in SSIS;




 Excellent command of the English language.

Evolution is a multinational business at the forefront of the online gaming industry. We have an extensive track record of number 1s and are always looking for great people to help us create the next big product hit. Our team of 1,000+ engineers operates out of 8 engineering hubs running code 24/7/365 to serve users around the world. This is run through a modern software stack that supports over 250 fully automated releases per month in our main live environment. We believe in building in-house competence and agile work processes so that we can deliver on our Engineering mission:
 *A flawless player experience.*
**Job Description**
 We appreciate all applications and interest in Evolution. This is a hybrid - role based in Stockholm, Sweden.




 We’re now looking for a motivated QA talent to join our amazing NetEnt team in Stockholm for a temporary position! As part of Evolution, a leader in one of the world’s fastest-growing industries, you’ll have the chance to help us break new ground and shape the future of gaming.




 Managing and ensuring the quality of a large portfolio of games is a core responsibility of our team. The role requires attention to detail and strong organizational skills to keep track of various game features, updates, and potential issues. Given the temporary nature of the role, it’s well-suited to someone who can quickly get up to speed with existing processes and workflows. With Evolution’s presence in the gaming industry, the position is ideal for you, with experience or interest in casino games.




 Responsibilities:




* Be a proactive member of our development team, collaborating closely with Product Owners, Designers, Developers, and other QA team members.
* Working alongside distributed teams to enhance collaboration and ensure seamless product delivery;
* Performing manual testing to validate features and requirements;
* Planning and executing test cases, writing test plans, and documenting bugs in detail;
* Participating in release process activities;
* Assessing product usability and reliability, providing valuable feedback and recommendations for improvements;
* Be prepared to learn, build your skills and knowledge, and share them with the team.


**Qualifications**
 Qualifications




* 3+ years of professional experience in software and functional testing;
* Understanding of software development processes, stages, concepts and methodologies of Quality Assurance;
* Experience in both web and mobile testing;
* Experience with Postman and version control systems (e.g., Git);
* Understanding of CI/CD pipelines and tools like Jenkins;
* Proficient in English, both written and spoken;
* Strong analytical and diagnostic skills, attention to details;
* Willingness to ask for help from colleagues and to help others.
* Nice-to-have:
* Experience with Kibana;
* Previous experience in casino games or related gaming environments;
* Knowledge of TypeScript basics, CSS, XPath.


**Additional Information**
 Exciting opportunity at our brand new office in the heart of Stockholm with amazing colleagues! Join our dynamic international team and be a part of a vibrant work environment where innovation thrives. Embrace the city´s energy as you contribute to our company´s growth!




 Evolution provides a dynamic and creative work environment with a unique opportunity for the right people to enhance their skills and drive their passion. Our culture is rooted in Evolution’s core values ALIVE, do RIGHT and work TOGETHER and we operate guided by our vision to become the leading supplier of online casino in the world.




**Our Benefits Are**
* Competitive pension, health and medical insurance
* 30 paid vacation days
* Fitness benefit (Friskvårdsbidrag)
* Professional growth
* Sport activities, parties, team buildings


 If you want to be part of one of the most exciting industries in the world, then apply now and be a key player in our success story!




 We appreciate all applications and interest in Evolution. This is a hybrid - role based in Stockholm, Sweden.
